There's no way that pitiful explosion
could destroy this ship!

24
00:02:16.910 --> 00:02:19.330
You mean it didn't work?!

25
00:02:19.330 --> 00:02:22.660
Of course not! It didn't even leave a scratch!

26
00:02:23.290 --> 00:02:26.460
The sails got burned, though...

27
00:02:30.760 --> 00:02:32.760
Sorry, Kin'emon!

28
00:02:32.760 --> 00:02:35.550
It took us a while to patch them up!

29
00:02:35.550 --> 00:02:36.930
I see!

30
00:02:36.930 --> 00:02:38.850
So that is what happened!

31
00:02:38.850 --> 00:02:40.640
Hey, Kin!

32
00:02:41.470 --> 00:02:44.480
Weren't there supposed
to be way more of you?!

33
00:02:45.190 --> 00:02:47.690
That's a little different than what I heard.

34
00:02:47.690 --> 00:02:50.610
Anyway, I'm gonna wreck those ships, okay?!

35
00:02:51.070 --> 00:02:52.190
Indeed...

36
00:02:52.190 --> 00:02:55.700
We were expecting a lot more allies.

37
00:02:56.950 --> 00:03:00.330
What happened to the 3,500 prisoners
from the mining camp?!

38
00:03:00.330 --> 00:03:02.160
Yeah, I don't see them.

39
00:03:02.620 --> 00:03:06.120
The bosses traveled to different
regions to gather the yakuza...

40
00:03:06.120 --> 00:03:09.290
There must've been over 200 of them.

41
00:03:09.290 --> 00:03:13.840
At Itachi Port, there were
200 of Inuarashi's Musketeers,

42
00:03:13.840 --> 00:03:17.840
and 280 of the Mount Atama Thieves!

43
00:03:17.840 --> 00:03:22.430
Everyone was supposed to meet us here
on the ships we repaired together!

44
00:03:22.430 --> 00:03:26.640
Plus a cache of weapons large enough
to arm every last one of them…

45
00:03:26.640 --> 00:03:29.270
should've been delivered from Ringo!

46
00:03:29.690 --> 00:03:31.730
Hey, Kin'emon!

47
00:03:31.730 --> 00:03:33.150
Did you run into trouble?!

48
00:03:44.330 --> 00:03:48.000
I... made a grave error...

49
00:03:50.380 --> 00:03:52.420
Sir Luffy, I am sorry!

50
00:03:53.090 --> 00:03:56.590
Our entire plan was leaked...

51
00:03:58.130 --> 00:04:01.720
I have no idea what's befallen the others!

52
00:04:02.140 --> 00:04:04.220
So that's why nobody came!

53
00:04:04.220 --> 00:04:06.390
Does that mean we're alone in the fight?!

54
00:04:06.390 --> 00:04:08.980
What?! No way!

55
00:04:08.980 --> 00:04:11.520
We don't really know what's going on, either!

56
00:04:11.520 --> 00:04:14.900
We might've failed to destroy the lion ship...

57
00:04:14.900 --> 00:04:19.700
...but we sank all the ships
docked at the port last night!

58
00:04:19.700 --> 00:04:22.410
Lord Orochi is a meticulous man.

59
00:04:22.740 --> 00:04:26.370
He ordered us to destroy
every major bridge connecting the regions!

60
00:04:27.750 --> 00:04:29.580
Do you get it now?

61
00:04:29.580 --> 00:04:33.000
Nobody's coming to save you!

62
00:04:33.000 --> 00:04:38.420
Even if they could get here, they won't
be able to reach Onigashima without ships!

63
00:04:38.420 --> 00:04:42.470
And if you miss this opportunity,
you'll never get another chance!

64
00:04:42.470 --> 00:04:47.430
Tomorrow, we'll start killing all the rebels
that we lured out, one by one!

65
00:04:48.940 --> 00:04:52.440
There's one more thing
we haven't mentioned yet!

66
00:04:52.440 --> 00:04:53.940
I'm sorry.

67
00:04:53.940 --> 00:04:56.980
We didn't want to plunge
you further into despair...

68
00:04:57.530 --> 00:04:58.740
What?!

69
00:04:59.070 --> 00:05:03.490
Today's banquet isn't an
ordinary Fire Festival feast...

70
00:05:03.870 --> 00:05:06.240
It's also a celebration...

71
00:05:06.240 --> 00:05:11.210
of the alliance between us, the Beast Pirates,
and the infamous Big Mom Pirates!

72
00:05:13.130 --> 00:05:15.170
Kaido and Big Mom?!

73
00:05:15.170 --> 00:05:17.210
An alliance of two Emperors?!

74
00:05:17.210 --> 00:05:21.220
We have both Captain Kaido
and Big Mom on our side!

75
00:05:21.220 --> 00:05:23.970
How can they hope to match
that kind of might?!

76
00:05:23.970 --> 00:05:26.760
The Worst Generation?! They're nothing!

77
00:05:26.760 --> 00:05:30.480
Let's sink them all and finish this!

78
00:05:30.480 --> 00:05:31.850
Get ready to fire!

79
00:05:39.400 --> 00:05:41.950
Why are you acting all high and mighty?!

80
00:05:43.030 --> 00:05:44.530
I've heard enough!

81
00:05:44.530 --> 00:05:45.910
Everyone, stand back!

82
00:05:46.240 --> 00:05:47.490
Imbecile...

83
00:05:47.490 --> 00:05:48.870
You stand back!

84
00:05:49.120 --> 00:05:49.200
What are you doing, Traffy?!

85
00:05:49.200 --> 00:05:49.290
What are you doing, Traffy?!

86
00:05:49.290 --> 00:05:50.790
What are you doing, Traffy?!

87
00:05:50.790 --> 00:05:53.170
I said I'll do it!

88
00:05:53.170 --> 00:05:54.380
As if you even could!

89
00:05:54.380 --> 00:05:57.040
No, both of you stand back!

90
00:05:57.040 --> 00:05:58.420
I'll do it!

91
00:05:58.750 --> 00:06:00.880
Screw you, Jaggy!

92
00:06:00.880 --> 00:06:02.720
Shut your mouth!

93
00:06:02.720 --> 00:06:02.800
Quit interrupting, you morons!

94
00:06:02.800 --> 00:06:02.880
Quit interrupting, you morons!

95
00:06:02.880 --> 00:06:04.840
Quit interrupting, you morons!

96
00:06:04.840 --> 00:06:05.890
Sheesh!

97
00:06:05.890 --> 00:06:07.390
First one there wins!

98
00:06:07.390 --> 00:06:08.970
You bastard!

99
00:06:08.970 --> 00:06:10.980
I'll be the first!

100
00:06:10.980 --> 00:06:12.100
Like hell you will!

101
00:06:18.270 --> 00:06:19.320
Traffy!

102
00:06:19.320 --> 00:06:20.530
Why you...!

103
00:06:20.530 --> 00:06:22.990
You can't outpace my
Room ability in rain!

104
00:06:22.990 --> 00:06:26.870
That's cheating! Your ability isn't fair!

105
00:06:26.870 --> 00:06:27.870
Who cares?

106
00:06:27.870 --> 00:06:30.160
You're just showing off!

107
00:06:30.160 --> 00:06:31.750
Look who's talking.

108
00:06:31.750 --> 00:06:33.290
Go away!

109
00:06:33.290 --> 00:06:35.330
I can take them out with a single blow!

110
00:06:35.330 --> 00:06:39.960
Are you trying to say
I can't do it in one shot?!

111
00:06:40.380 --> 00:06:41.510
I'll do it.

112
00:06:41.510 --> 00:06:43.550
You two are losers.

113
00:06:43.550 --> 00:06:44.970
Any complaints?

114
00:06:44.970 --> 00:06:46.640
– Losers?!
– Losers?!

115
00:06:46.640 --> 00:06:48.260
Who are you calling loser?!

116
00:06:48.260 --> 00:06:50.310
I won't lose to anyone!

117
00:06:50.310 --> 00:06:51.770
Stay out of my way!

118
00:06:51.770 --> 00:06:55.230
Y-You better not expect to
make it out of here alive!

119
00:06:55.230 --> 00:06:57.400
Stop barking, flunkies!

120
00:06:57.400 --> 00:06:59.070
I'll take care of them.

121
00:06:59.570 --> 00:07:00.650
Shut up!

122
00:07:00.650 --> 00:07:01.980
We'll see who's a loser!

123
00:07:06.820 --> 00:07:07.660
Room!

124
00:07:39.610 --> 00:07:41.690
Boundman!

125
00:07:48.320 --> 00:07:50.280
Punk Vise!

126
00:08:01.090 --> 00:08:02.840
Injection Shot!

127
00:08:35.750 --> 00:08:37.120
Hey, did you see that?

128
00:08:37.120 --> 00:08:39.210
Who's a loser now?!

129
00:08:39.540 --> 00:08:41.500
Let me make one thing clear.

130
00:08:42.210 --> 00:08:44.920
I'm the one who sank that ship.

131
00:08:44.920 --> 00:08:46.920
Are you blind?!

132
00:08:47.340 --> 00:08:48.550
Don't be stupid!

133
00:08:48.550 --> 00:08:50.470
I sank it!

134
00:08:50.470 --> 00:08:53.640
I thought they were allies...

135
00:08:57.890 --> 00:08:58.600
What's that...?!

136
00:09:00.730 --> 00:09:02.810
The Kyoshiro Family's ship!

137
00:09:02.810 --> 00:09:05.070
Kyoshiro's here!

138
00:09:05.070 --> 00:09:07.530
Now the show can go on!

139
00:09:07.530 --> 00:09:09.860
Seems like you're in trouble.

140
00:09:09.860 --> 00:09:15.200
All we have to do is sink the Red Scabbards,
as Lord Orochi ordered us to!

141
00:09:15.580 --> 00:09:16.620
Alright.

142
00:09:16.620 --> 00:09:18.910
Sink the enemy, you say?

143
00:09:18.910 --> 00:09:20.000
Allow me!

144
00:09:24.880 --> 00:09:27.510
What are you doing, Boss?!

145
00:09:34.220 --> 00:09:36.220
There was no need to sink the ship.

146
00:09:36.220 --> 00:09:40.310
Though I did take the liberty of
disabling the cannons pointed at us.

147
00:09:40.310 --> 00:09:42.810
That guy... I remember him!

148
00:09:42.810 --> 00:09:45.820
Be careful! He's a master of the blade!

149
00:09:45.820 --> 00:09:48.070
He's the shogun's dog!

150
00:09:48.070 --> 00:09:51.780
A man of chivalry who took
the place of Boss Hyogoro!

151
00:09:54.740 --> 00:09:56.990
Red Scabbards samurai!

152
00:09:57.450 --> 00:10:00.700
I am a yakuza from the Flower Capital!

153
00:10:00.700 --> 00:10:03.420
People call me Napping Kyoshiro!

154
00:10:03.870 --> 00:10:09.590
The Kyoshiro Family is 200 strong!
Please allow us to join your raid!

155
00:10:10.380 --> 00:10:11.550
– What?!
– What?!

156
00:10:11.550 --> 00:10:13.090
You've gotta be kidding, Boss!

157
00:10:13.090 --> 00:10:14.510
What do you mean?!

158
00:10:14.510 --> 00:10:16.140
You're Orochi's subordinate!

159
00:10:16.140 --> 00:10:18.100
What obligation do you have to help us?

160
00:10:21.270 --> 00:10:26.020
The duty and gratitude I hold toward
the Kozuki Clan are immeasurable…

161
00:10:29.230 --> 00:10:31.940
I remember you especially, Kin!

162
00:10:32.860 --> 00:10:34.110
Kin?!

163
00:10:34.110 --> 00:10:38.490
Forty years ago, the Mountain God
Incident shook the capital!

164
00:10:41.910 --> 00:10:45.290
People blamed it on Lord Oden running wild...

165
00:10:46.170 --> 00:10:47.920
But they were wrong.

166
00:10:47.920 --> 00:10:54.800
You were the cause: a greedy young man
trying to sell a little boar!

167
00:10:59.220 --> 00:11:00.390
What?

168
00:11:00.390 --> 00:11:03.430
Only one man could possibly know that!

169
00:11:05.440 --> 00:11:08.270
That's why they call it the Mountain God!

170
00:11:08.270 --> 00:11:09.480
What?!

171
00:11:09.480 --> 00:11:11.400
Oh no!

172
00:11:11.400 --> 00:11:13.900
I've brought this upon the capital!

173
00:11:15.820 --> 00:11:16.950
Could it be...?

174
00:11:17.450 --> 00:11:18.950
Is that you, Denjiro?!

175
00:11:18.950 --> 00:11:19.580
What?!

176
00:11:19.580 --> 00:11:20.580
Denjiro?!

177
00:11:26.290 --> 00:11:28.080
Exactly right!

178
00:11:28.080 --> 00:11:29.920
I suppose you may not recognize me...

179
00:11:30.960 --> 00:11:33.510
I wanted to reveal myself to you right away,

180
00:11:33.510 --> 00:11:36.880
but I remained an enemy, just in case.

181
00:11:36.880 --> 00:11:39.760
Sure enough, if I had revealed my identity,

182
00:11:39.760 --> 00:11:44.640
I would've been exposed by
Orochi's spy and snuffed out!

183
00:11:46.350 --> 00:11:47.600
Denjiro!

184
00:11:47.600 --> 00:11:49.400
Silence!

185
00:11:49.400 --> 00:11:53.190
However, since I kept
Orochi's trust until the end,

186
00:11:53.190 --> 00:11:58.070
I was able to free the 1,000 samurai
from Rasetsu Prison!

187
00:11:58.070 --> 00:11:59.240
Look over there!

188
00:11:59.240 --> 00:12:00.410
Enemy reinforcements?!

189
00:12:02.030 --> 00:12:04.160
We now have 1,200 soldiers!

190
00:12:04.160 --> 00:12:06.410
Let us bolster your ranks!

191
00:12:12.290 --> 00:12:14.210
The time has finally come!

192
00:12:14.210 --> 00:12:16.010
At last, we get to fight!

193
00:12:16.010 --> 00:12:20.510
B-Boss Kyoshiro is one
of the Nine Red Scabbards?!

194
00:12:20.510 --> 00:12:23.010
Alert Onigashima immediately!

195
00:12:23.010 --> 00:12:24.560
Y-Yeah!

196
00:12:31.400 --> 00:12:32.730
Denjiro...

197
00:12:33.270 --> 00:12:34.570
Now then, Kin!

198
00:12:34.570 --> 00:12:35.150
Huh?

199
00:12:35.150 --> 00:12:37.820
I knew you were a clever man!

200
00:12:37.820 --> 00:12:42.280
This symbol implies the date
and rendezvous point for the great battle!

201
00:12:42.280 --> 00:12:44.660
Two birds ablaze…

202
00:12:45.240 --> 00:12:47.000
over a habu pit viper...

203
00:12:47.000 --> 00:12:51.130
and a reversed crescent moon
to signify rebellion!

204
00:12:51.130 --> 00:12:54.840
“The day of the Fire Festival. At twilight.
The second hour of the bird.

205
00:12:54.840 --> 00:12:57.260
At Habu Port."

206
00:12:57.260 --> 00:13:00.220
The original symbol didn't have those two lines.

207
00:13:01.760 --> 00:13:05.760
This flyer was leaked to Orochi's side...

208
00:13:06.520 --> 00:13:11.730
but Lord Yasuie altered
the symbol before he died!

209
00:13:11.730 --> 00:13:14.400
These two newly added lines...

210
00:13:14.400 --> 00:13:18.360
cross out the middle letters!

211
00:13:18.360 --> 00:13:23.030
So "Habuminato" without the middle part
means the new rendezvous point is...

212
00:13:18.360 --> 00:13:23.530
Habuminato

213
00:13:22.700 --> 00:13:22.780
/

214
00:13:22.780 --> 00:13:22.870
/

215
00:13:22.870 --> 00:13:23.530
/

216
00:13:22.950 --> 00:13:23.030
/

217
00:13:23.030 --> 00:13:23.530
/

218
00:13:23.530 --> 00:13:24.740
"Hato"!

219
00:13:23.530 --> 00:13:23.570
Hato

220
00:13:23.570 --> 00:13:23.610
Hato

221
00:13:23.610 --> 00:13:23.650
Hato

222
00:13:23.650 --> 00:13:23.690
Hato

223
00:13:23.690 --> 00:13:23.740
Hato

224
00:13:23.740 --> 00:13:23.780
Hato

225
00:13:23.780 --> 00:13:23.820
Hato

226
00:13:23.820 --> 00:13:24.990
Hato

227
00:13:24.580 --> 00:13:26.540
Wharf
(Hato)

228
00:13:26.540 --> 00:13:26.580
Wharf
(Hato)

229
00:13:26.580 --> 00:13:26.620
Wharf
(Hato)

230
00:13:26.620 --> 00:13:26.660
(Hato)

231
00:13:28.200 --> 00:13:29.960
You chose the wharf at Habu Port.

232
00:13:29.960 --> 00:13:33.960
Lord Yasuie always loved
the stunning vistas of its maple forest!

233
00:13:35.460 --> 00:13:36.050
What?

234
00:13:36.050 --> 00:13:37.920
What?!

235
00:13:37.920 --> 00:13:43.470
Seeing two lines over a habu pit viper,
anyone would easily get that message.

236
00:13:45.470 --> 00:13:49.520
But you deduced that
Orochi's spy was in your ranks,

237
00:13:49.520 --> 00:13:54.810
and purposely misread the answer
to them as "Tokage Port"!

238
00:13:55.190 --> 00:14:00.030
Wano's ports are all named after animals.

239
00:14:00.030 --> 00:14:04.450
It's a bit long, but adding legs
to the viper makes a tokage lizard:

240
00:14:04.450 --> 00:14:06.990
Tokage Port in Udon.

241
00:14:08.870 --> 00:14:13.290
It's true... that picture didn't look like a lizard.

242
00:14:13.290 --> 00:14:17.340
I believed it because Kin was so confident...

243
00:14:17.340 --> 00:14:20.460
The spy fell for your ruse...

244
00:14:21.010 --> 00:14:24.800
and told Orochi that Tokage Port
was the new rendezvous point!

245
00:14:26.600 --> 00:14:30.350
That is the folly of a tyrant
who languished in the capital for too long!

246
00:14:30.350 --> 00:14:35.650
Orochi misjudged the distance between
each region and sat idle until last night!

247
00:14:35.650 --> 00:14:40.360
By that time, everyone
had crossed the great bridges,

248
00:14:40.940 --> 00:14:43.950
and the ships they needed had left the port!

249
00:14:43.950 --> 00:14:46.240
Only the leftover ships were destroyed!

250
00:14:46.660 --> 00:14:50.870
Just as you planned, the 4,200
troops that you recruited...

251
00:14:51.290 --> 00:14:55.000
were lying low at the Habu Port
wharf until the time came!

252
00:14:56.080 --> 00:14:58.000
Then everyone is safe?!

253
00:15:13.520 --> 00:15:18.480
Even after twenty years, I still remember
Lord Oden's legendary death!

254
00:15:18.860 --> 00:15:22.650
We have lived our lives believing
in the return of the Kozuki Clan!

255
00:15:23.030 --> 00:15:26.360
We are coming with you,
Red Scabbards samurai!

256
00:15:26.360 --> 00:15:28.490
Everything is in place!

257
00:15:31.080 --> 00:15:35.410
The raid on Onigashima
will go exactly as planned!

258
00:15:36.670 --> 00:15:41.040
Adding 1,200 of us makes it 5,400 in total!

259
00:15:41.040 --> 00:15:43.550
Now, let's go, everyone!

260
00:15:48.010 --> 00:15:49.850
To Onigashima!

261
00:15:53.100 --> 00:15:54.560
Check that out!

262
00:15:56.350 --> 00:16:00.020
I don't really know what happened,
but I guess it's all good now!

263
00:16:00.020 --> 00:16:01.820
There are tons of them!

264
00:16:01.820 --> 00:16:04.110
This is a disaster!

265
00:16:04.110 --> 00:16:05.990
Anything from Onigashima?!

266
00:16:05.990 --> 00:16:10.120
I've been calling, but no one's picked up!
They're probably busy with the banquet!

267
00:16:11.030 --> 00:16:12.410
What a calamity!

268
00:16:12.410 --> 00:16:14.830
We've thwarted nothing!

269
00:16:14.830 --> 00:16:18.080
Damn you, Kin'emon!

270
00:16:18.750 --> 00:16:20.080
Kin!

271
00:16:20.080 --> 00:16:22.290
You truly are our leader!

272
00:16:22.290 --> 00:16:24.960
And as expected, a man
worthy of my respect!

273
00:16:38.440 --> 00:16:40.440
So it wasn't "tokage"...

274
00:16:41.100 --> 00:16:43.110
It meant "hato," the wharf...

275
00:16:52.870 --> 00:16:55.830
Be honest, Kin'emon.

276
00:16:55.830 --> 00:17:00.750
We know there's no way you could
come up with something like that.

277
00:17:01.670 --> 00:17:03.170
Look, it turned out fine.

278
00:17:03.170 --> 00:17:04.800
We won't get mad, so just admit it.

279
00:17:04.800 --> 00:17:05.500
Stop.

280
00:17:06.050 --> 00:17:09.300
You actually thought it was
"tokage," didn't you?

281
00:17:09.300 --> 00:17:10.180
Stop it!

282
00:17:10.590 --> 00:17:12.720
Well, it turned out fine in the end!

283
00:17:12.720 --> 00:17:14.010
It was a lucky mistake.

284
00:17:17.310 --> 00:17:20.850
Perhaps this battle will be my last.

285
00:17:22.020 --> 00:17:25.360
I feel like I just used up
a lifetime's worth of luck!

286
00:17:27.230 --> 00:17:29.610
Indeed, you have shockingly good luck!

287
00:17:29.610 --> 00:17:31.030
Kin'emon!

288
00:17:31.030 --> 00:17:32.780
Our beloved leader!

289
00:17:32.780 --> 00:17:38.910
Then our luck was used as well,
since we share the same ambition!

290
00:17:42.620 --> 00:17:44.330
He's right, Kin!

291
00:17:44.330 --> 00:17:46.130
We won't let you die alone!

292
00:17:46.500 --> 00:17:49.210
We served Lord Oden together as samurai!

293
00:17:49.210 --> 00:17:53.970
Our pasts may differ, but our last stand
will be as one! Remember that!

294
00:18:02.350 --> 00:18:06.230
That's cold comfort coming
from you hoodlums.

295
00:18:08.980 --> 00:18:10.990
Raise your sword, Kin!

296
00:18:10.990 --> 00:18:13.450
We already won the opening bout!

297
00:18:18.950 --> 00:18:21.370
Let us fulfill our destiny.

298
00:18:22.410 --> 00:18:25.380
We shall avenge Lord Oden's death together!

299
00:18:26.790 --> 00:18:29.050
Kin'emon!

300
00:18:29.050 --> 00:18:32.300
We will bring change to Wano at any cost!

301
00:18:37.430 --> 00:18:39.220
Damn that Kin'emon...

302
00:18:39.220 --> 00:18:40.970
I must report to Onigashima.

303
00:18:40.970 --> 00:18:44.390
I have fulfilled the role
that Lord Orochi cast me in!

304
00:18:46.020 --> 00:18:48.150
There's just one thing left to do!

305
00:18:56.490 --> 00:18:57.620
Oh, no, you don't!

306
00:18:58.410 --> 00:19:01.660
I won't let you take Lord Momonosuke!

307
00:19:06.170 --> 00:19:08.340
Kawamatsu! Hold on, I'm coming!

308
00:19:08.340 --> 00:19:10.710
You can't! You'll drown!

309
00:19:10.710 --> 00:19:15.220
Do you take pleasure in stomping
on our dreams and making us despair?

310
00:19:15.220 --> 00:19:17.180
Kanjuro!

311
00:19:18.510 --> 00:19:21.430
Yes! I'm having the time of my life!

312
00:19:22.350 --> 00:19:25.350
Deception, betrayal,
and then a twist ending!

313
00:19:25.350 --> 00:19:28.110
There's no play in the
world that could top this!

314
00:19:29.940 --> 00:19:33.570
And you all played the stooge perfectly!

315
00:19:36.610 --> 00:19:39.700
Kanjuro!

316
00:19:44.080 --> 00:19:48.330
The final act will paint
the stage red with Kozuki blood!

317
00:19:55.470 --> 00:19:57.300
Kawamatsu!

318
00:19:57.300 --> 00:19:59.140
Lord Momonosuke!

319
00:19:59.550 --> 00:20:01.300
Don't worry, Momonosuke.

320
00:20:01.300 --> 00:20:04.060
I'll let your sister follow you into death.

321
00:20:04.060 --> 00:20:05.310
Kawamatsu!

322
00:20:05.310 --> 00:20:08.270
I swear I'll find Hiyori and kill her, too!

323
00:20:08.270 --> 00:20:10.940
Now that I know she's alive!

324
00:20:14.400 --> 00:20:15.990
Kanjuro!

325
00:20:15.990 --> 00:20:19.160
Since when can you draw
a bird that flies so elegantly?!

326
00:20:19.160 --> 00:20:25.250
All we ever saw were horrible scribbles
that washed away with water!

327
00:20:26.000 --> 00:20:27.330
It's too high!

328
00:20:27.330 --> 00:20:28.920
Let me down!

329
00:20:28.920 --> 00:20:29.790
It's too scary!

330
00:20:29.790 --> 00:20:31.170
Somebody!

331
00:20:31.670 --> 00:20:32.790
Kanjuro?

332
00:20:32.790 --> 00:20:33.840
Momo?

333
00:20:33.840 --> 00:20:35.510
Hey! Where are you going?!

334
00:20:35.510 --> 00:20:37.920
Farewell, you fools!

335
00:20:41.180 --> 00:20:45.430
No matter what you try,
you won't beat Lord Kaido's army!

336
00:20:45.430 --> 00:20:48.140
You'll never even set foot on the island!

337
00:20:51.940 --> 00:20:56.860
Help!

338
00:20:56.860 --> 00:20:58.240
Wait!

339
00:20:58.240 --> 00:20:59.910
Lord Momonosuke!

340
00:20:59.910 --> 00:21:02.700
Kanjuro of the Red Scabbards betrayed us!

341
00:21:02.700 --> 00:21:04.620
Lord Momonosuke!

342
00:21:04.620 --> 00:21:05.910
Why?!

343
00:21:08.210 --> 00:21:12.790
That makes Kanjuro a spy then, right, Robin?

344
00:21:12.790 --> 00:21:14.170
So it seems.

345
00:21:14.170 --> 00:21:15.750
We must help Momo!

346
00:21:15.750 --> 00:21:17.710
What?!

347
00:21:24.260 --> 00:21:25.850
Luffy!

348
00:21:25.850 --> 00:21:29.100
Kanjuro was a spy for the enemy!

349
00:21:29.100 --> 00:21:31.600
He's taking Momo away!

350
00:21:31.600 --> 00:21:32.520
What?!

351
00:21:32.520 --> 00:21:34.020
Are you sure?!

352
00:21:34.020 --> 00:21:37.150
So he's been lying to us the whole time?!

353
00:21:38.860 --> 00:21:40.700
That bastard!

354
00:21:44.950 --> 00:21:46.830
He's flying into the clouds!

355
00:21:47.240 --> 00:21:48.620
I'll shoot him down!

356
00:21:50.250 --> 00:21:54.840
Lethal Green Star: Platanus Shuriken!

357
00:22:01.220 --> 00:22:03.260
It's a shame, but...

358
00:22:03.260 --> 00:22:06.760
I don't have time for you amateurs!

359
00:22:18.070 --> 00:22:19.940
What with this cloud?!

360
00:22:19.940 --> 00:22:21.610
No, Sir Sanji!

361
00:22:21.610 --> 00:22:22.950
Get back!

362
00:22:22.950 --> 00:22:24.490
I have a bad feeling!

363
00:22:26.700 --> 00:22:29.410
I bet it's another technique
we've never seen...

364
00:22:29.410 --> 00:22:31.410
Ink Clouds!

365
00:22:35.290 --> 00:22:37.380
Let the ink arrows rain down!

366
00:22:46.510 --> 00:22:49.560
Ukiyo Portrait: Evening Tempest!

367
00:22:55.980 --> 00:22:57.310
Hard aport!

368
00:22:57.310 --> 00:22:59.020
Get away from the cloud!

369
00:23:02.860 --> 00:23:03.780
No!

370
00:23:03.780 --> 00:23:05.110
Nami!

371
00:23:08.580 --> 00:23:12.790
The only person who's allowed to shoot
an arrow through Nami and Robin's hearts...

372
00:23:12.790 --> 00:23:15.870
is me!

373
00:23:15.870 --> 00:23:17.380
Sanji!

374
00:23:19.750 --> 00:23:22.880
Stop already, Kanjuro!

375
00:23:22.880 --> 00:23:26.340
They're all going to die!

376
00:23:26.340 --> 00:23:27.390
That's right...

377
00:23:28.220 --> 00:23:30.470
They're all going to die...

378
00:23:31.180 --> 00:23:32.560
at long last!

379
00:23:34.310 --> 00:23:36.770
Your father Oden,

380
00:23:37.270 --> 00:23:40.480
and your mother Toki held out false hope,

381
00:23:41.150 --> 00:23:45.860
merely letting those idiots
escape death for twenty years...

382
00:23:49.910 --> 00:23:56.920
I find it quite amusing that the leader
of those fierce, vengeful samurai...

383
00:23:56.920 --> 00:24:02.840
is just a cowardly child
who's scared of heights.

384
00:24:08.260 --> 00:24:10.720
Now that's a comedy!

385
00:24:11.100 --> 00:24:13.140
I know...

386
00:24:15.980 --> 00:24:19.980
I am not Kozuki Oden...

387
00:24:19.980 --> 00:24:22.570
I know that better than anyone!

388
00:24:27.320 --> 00:24:28.820
What should I do?!

389
00:24:28.820 --> 00:24:29.910
I can't do anything...

390
00:24:31.530 --> 00:24:32.990
E...

391
00:24:32.990 --> 00:24:34.480
Ev...

392
00:24:35.870 --> 00:24:38.040
What am I trying to say?!

393
00:24:38.830 --> 00:24:42.750
If I say something like that,
no one is going to help me!

394
00:24:44.210 --> 00:24:45.300
But...

395
00:24:52.180 --> 00:24:53.890
Everyone!

396
00:24:53.890 --> 00:24:59.730
Can you hear me?!

397
00:24:59.730 --> 00:25:01.150
Lord Momonosuke!

398
00:25:02.230 --> 00:25:06.740
All of you, do not worry about me!

399
00:25:07.690 --> 00:25:11.820
That is exactly what they want!

400
00:25:12.990 --> 00:25:16.790
I shall escape on my own!

401
00:25:16.790 --> 00:25:23.170
So I call on you to bring down
Kaido and Orochi and save Wano!

402
00:25:28.840 --> 00:25:33.470
He speaks with such noble purity!

403
00:25:34.180 --> 00:25:35.890
Lord Momonosuke!

404
00:25:38.020 --> 00:25:40.190
Lord Momonosuke!

405
00:25:40.730 --> 00:25:44.060
Puny little Momo stood up like a man...

406
00:25:46.900 --> 00:25:48.360
That's right, Momo!

407
00:25:50.030 --> 00:25:51.240
You...

408
00:25:51.950 --> 00:25:55.030
might be just a stupid little scaredy-cat,

409
00:25:55.370 --> 00:25:59.080
but you sure can act high and mighty,
you topknot pipsqueak!

410
00:25:59.080 --> 00:26:02.080
How dare he speak so rudely
to Lord Momonosuke?!

411
00:26:02.080 --> 00:26:03.420
Who is that bastard?!

412
00:26:03.420 --> 00:26:04.880
Chop him up!

413
00:26:05.540 --> 00:26:07.750
Keep yourself alive!

414
00:26:07.750 --> 00:26:11.840
I'll rescue you for sure!

415
00:26:15.050 --> 00:26:16.390
Because we're pals!

416
00:26:40.410 --> 00:26:41.410
Alright...

417
00:26:44.580 --> 00:26:46.790
Let's go to Onigashima!

418
00:26:46.790 --> 00:26:48.500
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

419
00:27:04.600 --> 00:27:05.980
Luffy!

420
00:27:05.980 --> 00:27:08.770
One of the enemy ships is fleeing!

421
00:27:10.280 --> 00:27:11.480
Let it go!

422
00:27:11.480 --> 00:27:15.610
We're gonna head that direction
anyway, so we can sink it later!

423
00:27:16.700 --> 00:27:19.530
Huh?! I thought there was one more ship.

424
00:27:19.530 --> 00:27:21.490
Oh, yeah, I already sank it.

425
00:27:24.040 --> 00:27:27.040
Kin! Forgive me!

426
00:27:27.040 --> 00:27:29.170
I should have saved him!

427
00:27:29.170 --> 00:27:31.130
I'm just glad that you are safe.

428
00:27:31.130 --> 00:27:34.300
I do not think they will take
Lord Momonosuke's life yet.

429
00:27:34.760 --> 00:27:37.010
By the way, Denjiro!

430
00:27:37.010 --> 00:27:38.340
What...

431
00:27:39.050 --> 00:27:40.850
happened to your face?!

432
00:27:43.850 --> 00:27:45.980
It's a long story.

433
00:27:47.980 --> 00:27:50.190
I'm glad to see you all!

434
00:27:50.190 --> 00:27:52.110
Everyone!

435
00:27:52.110 --> 00:27:53.360
Are you all right?!

436
00:27:53.360 --> 00:27:57.530
There are some injuries and wrecked ships!

437
00:27:57.530 --> 00:27:59.950
Let's hurry and land on the island!

438
00:27:59.950 --> 00:28:03.580
We'd hate to die at sea!

439
00:28:03.580 --> 00:28:04.450
Hey!

440
00:28:06.040 --> 00:28:09.000
This isn't some samurai day care!

441
00:28:12.750 --> 00:28:13.960
– We are in your care.
– We are in your care.

442
00:28:14.960 --> 00:28:16.670
No, you're not!

443
00:28:16.670 --> 00:28:17.680
Get off!

444
00:28:18.510 --> 00:28:19.970
Guys!

445
00:28:20.430 --> 00:28:22.930
Don't fall behind the Straw Hats!

446
00:28:22.930 --> 00:28:24.560
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

447
00:28:30.610 --> 00:28:32.610
What?! Where did that come from?!

448
00:28:34.820 --> 00:28:36.650
It came from the ship that fled!

449
00:28:38.490 --> 00:28:40.030
A long-range cannon?!

450
00:28:40.030 --> 00:28:43.080
They were just building distance!

451
00:28:43.080 --> 00:28:45.750
How can they hit us from that far?!

452
00:28:50.880 --> 00:28:54.800
Wano weaponry is top-grade!

453
00:28:55.170 --> 00:29:03.510
Thanks to the factories in Wano,
we Beast Pirates have a vast arsenal!

454
00:29:03.510 --> 00:29:08.100
Try flying at us like you did before!

455
00:29:13.650 --> 00:29:14.860
Back the ship up!

456
00:29:14.860 --> 00:29:16.570
We're too close!

457
00:29:27.830 --> 00:29:31.000
Damn! I knew they retreated too eagerly...

458
00:29:33.580 --> 00:29:35.300
Full speed ahead!

459
00:29:35.300 --> 00:29:36.800
We gotta get closer!

460
00:29:40.220 --> 00:29:44.180
I don't care how many
samurai ships they sink!

461
00:29:51.690 --> 00:29:52.690
Oh no!

462
00:29:52.690 --> 00:29:54.730
If they keep this distance...

463
00:29:56.070 --> 00:29:58.280
we'll all go down!

464
00:30:05.030 --> 00:30:06.990
It's over now!

465
00:30:07.450 --> 00:30:10.160
There's nothing they can do!

466
00:30:20.670 --> 00:30:22.630
Fire! Fire!

467
00:30:27.310 --> 00:30:30.890
Fishman Karate:

468
00:30:30.890 --> 00:30:34.230
Spear Wave!

469
00:30:52.250 --> 00:30:53.290
Hull breach!

470
00:30:53.290 --> 00:30:54.370
Help!

471
00:30:54.370 --> 00:30:55.380
I'm falling!

472
00:31:01.170 --> 00:31:04.380
Fishman Karate:

473
00:31:04.380 --> 00:31:08.930
Spear Wave Rain Shower!

474
00:31:19.440 --> 00:31:21.730
The long-range cannons...!

475
00:31:25.240 --> 00:31:27.070
Something's happening.

476
00:31:27.450 --> 00:31:29.910
Maybe the ghost of a drowned baby...

477
00:31:30.450 --> 00:31:32.160
is killing them...

478
00:31:32.950 --> 00:31:35.960
That sounds peaceful compared to this!

479
00:31:35.960 --> 00:31:37.290
What's going on?!

480
00:31:46.880 --> 00:31:48.140
Who's out there?

481
00:31:50.760 --> 00:31:52.470
Everyone!

482
00:31:53.140 --> 00:31:55.440
If I may have your attention...!

483
00:31:58.770 --> 00:32:01.900
I was born...

484
00:32:01.900 --> 00:32:07.110
in the Fishman District of the Ryugu Kingdom,
at the bottom of the sea...

485
00:32:09.990 --> 00:32:15.960
I've given those I've served under
a great deal of trouble.

486
00:32:16.330 --> 00:32:22.460
And now, I drink from the
sake cup of Boss Straw Hat...

487
00:32:22.960 --> 00:32:25.840
as a mere fledgling of this crew!

488
00:32:30.510 --> 00:32:32.600
People call me...

489
00:32:32.600 --> 00:32:36.100
Jinbe, Knight of the Sea!

490
00:32:36.100 --> 00:32:38.810
Jinbe, "Knight of the Sea"

491
00:32:39.190 --> 00:32:40.770
You've got to be kidding.

492
00:32:40.770 --> 00:32:43.980
He's gonna join the Straw Hats?!

493
00:32:43.980 --> 00:32:54.160
Jinbe, "Knight of the Sea"

Helmsman of the Straw Hat Pirates
Bounty: 438 Million Belly

494
00:32:45.490 --> 00:32:48.950
I humbly present myself,

495
00:32:48.950 --> 00:32:52.330
and look forward to our harmonious kinship!

496
00:32:59.250 --> 00:33:01.130
– Jinbe!
– Jinbe!

497
00:33:01.130 --> 00:33:02.420
– Boss!
– Boss!

498
00:33:02.420 --> 00:33:04.250
– Jinbe!
– Jinbe!

499
00:33:06.800 --> 00:33:10.800
Thank you for indulging me!

500
00:33:10.800 --> 00:33:11.930
Luffy!

501
00:33:11.930 --> 00:33:14.930
I came back alive as I promised you!

502
00:33:15.260 --> 00:33:18.100
I'm glad I made it in time for the battle!
